    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-25T00:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-24T10:07:00-05:00" n="359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.01/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-01-25T00:44:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1919-01-24T20:00:00+04:53">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 24, 1919, 12:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at] Omsk.</p>
                <p>“51. January 24, 8 p.m. Sir <persName corresp="#p_ESC1">Charles Eliot</persName>
                    <note n="50" xml:id="d359fn50">British High Commissioner in Siberia.</note> has
                    officially stated to the Foreign Office here on behalf of his Government that,
                    inasmuch as the Omsk Government now represents the highest Russian power, Great
                    Britain expresses its warmest sympathy with <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> endeavors to create a free Russian Government on the
                    basis of public confidence as only under such conditions can Russia return to
                    its former place among the nations and partake in the upbuilding of
                    civilization.</p>
                <p>On January 21 Ambassador Regnault<note n="51" xml:id="d359fn51">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CGEB1">Eugéne Louis Georges</persName> Regnault,
                        French High Commissioner in Siberia.</note> handed <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> a communication from the French
                    Government in which it expressed its pleasure at the union which has been
                    attained between the <persName corresp="#p_DGAI">Denikin</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> governments. At the same
                    time the French Government <pb facs="0440" n="328" xml:id="pg_328"/> expressed
                    satisfaction at the choice of Sazonoff as the common Minister of Foreign Affairs
                    of both. They point out way for the recognition of <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Admiral Kolchak</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1"
                    >Harris</persName>.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
